description:
After two years I decided to remaster my previous poster :)
I added five new objects nad many of them are processed again.
Also stars backgroung was replaced - I made it using stars from Cheeseburger Nebula photo - starfield is randomized :) There is no real configuration there.

All of the photographs were made using lucky-imaging / short-exposure technique with exp times from 1s to 20 seconds (without guiding)
That's why details in all of the nebulas is really nice.
Resolution of photo is 0,55'/pix

Data collected using 350/1400 and 250/1200 Newtonian telescopes with ASI 178 MM-C camera on NEQ-6 mount

Full 41 MPix resolution (with scale 0,23''/pix)  poster is avaiable for printout here:

https://pixels.com/featured/hearts-of-dying-stars-lukasz-sujka.html
title: Planetary Nebulae (2020 remastered)
